OL,7,F"This is key in proving that simple,
OL,8,Fsmall pockets of time connecting with
OL,9,Fwildlife and nature have a profound
OL,10,Fand beneficial effect on how we feel."
OL,12,FParticipants reported a range of
OL,13,Fpositive and negative emotions,
OL,14,Fincluding joy, fascination, sadness,
OL,15,Fand concern.
OL,17,FThe feeling of concern was driven by
OL,18,Fnot seeing as many butterflies as they
OL,19,Fexpected and fear over what is
OL,20,Fhappening to the planet.
